GEO:39.171255;-86.516556
SUMMARY:Total African Cinema Exhibit
DESCRIPTION:Donated by the Vieyra family in June 2021\, the exhibition sh
 owcases highlights from The Paulin S. Vieyra Collection. The display case
  features intimate and rare items\, including family portraits\, Vieyra's
  typewriter\, and a 16mm reel of MĂ´l (1966). Five original collages by g
 raphic designer Pouya Jahanshahi are at the center of the exhibition. Jah
 anshahi collaborated with Project Archivist Jason Byrne\, who shaped the 
 exhibition's themes and selected archival content. Student workers Sarah 
 Petras\, Thomas Pigott\, Cree Prince\, and Kudzai Zinyemba supported the 
 project by helping process and research the materials.  The TOTAL AFRICAN
  CINEMA exhibit is on view in the BFCA reception area now through May 31\
 , 2026!
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Donated by the Vieyra family in June 20
 21\, the exhibition showcases highlights from The Paulin S. Vieyra Collec
 tion. The display case features intimate and rare items\, including famil
 y portraits\, Vieyra's typewriter\, and a 16mm reel of <em>MĂ´l</em> (196
 6). Five original collages by graphic designer Pouya Jahanshahi are at th
 e center of the exhibition. Jahanshahi collaborated with Project Archivis
 t Jason Byrne\, who shaped the exhibition's themes and selected archival 
 content. Student workers Sarah Petras\, Thomas Pigott\, Cree Prince\, and
  Kudzai Zinyemba supported the project by helping process and research th
 e materials.</p><p>  The <em>TOTAL AFRICAN CINEMA</em> exhibit is on view
  in the BFCA reception area now through May 31\, 2026!</p>
